  "prompt": "Why does Ramsay Bolton treat Sansa Stark that way on their wedding night?",
  "response": "Ramsay Bolton's behavior towards Sansa Stark on their wedding night in the TV series \"Game of Thrones\" is a reflection of his cruel and sadistic nature. Ramsay is depicted as a character who derives pleasure from exerting power and inflicting pain on others. His treatment of Sansa is not only a way to establish dominance over her but also a means to assert control and instill fear. This scene is a significant moment in the series, highlighting Ramsay's brutality and adding to the perilous situation that Sansa finds herself in. It serves to emphasize the dark and violent world of Westeros and the personal challenges Sansa must overcome.",
